--- Round 1 ---
A1 (contrarian debater): Guaranteeing basic necessities as a universal right frees people from survival anxiety, enabling them to pursue meaningful work, fostering innovation, and reducing inequality.
A2 (contrarian debater): Earning basic necessities through work instills personal responsibility, ensures equitable resource allocation, and maintains economic stability. When individuals contribute labor, they value the goods they receive, reducing dependency and fostering a productive society.
MODERATOR (Summary): Debater A1, you highlighted how guaranteed necessities reduce anxiety and spur innovation; Debater A2, you emphasized responsibility and stability through work. Debater A1, given A2’s point about equitable resource allocation, is there an aspect you can agree with or build upon? Debaters, both value a productive society—how might that shared value guide a compromise? It’s now Debater A1’s turn.

